----------------------------------------------------------------------
-- Whole-model verification summary
----------------------------------------------------------------------

-- Summary 1: Fixed type errors by adding concrete Resource sigs (DatabaseResource, APIResource) and updated all references that previously mixed Interface and Resource.
-- Summary 2: Removed contradictory NFR facts (e.g., requiring exactly 2 channels per operation) that caused all run predicates to become unsatisfiable.
-- Summary 3: Rewrote edge-case assertion ec_safe_1 to use proper Resource types.
-- Assumption 1: The model assumes that the system state (Pre1, Post1, Post2, Post3) adequately represents the workflow of accepting, storing, and assigning a unique ID to a transfusion request.
-- Assumption 2: The unique identifier is modeled as a resource whose owner is the initiator (logging).
-- Open issue 1: The model does not explicitly enforce that a unique identifier is truly unique (e.g., no two operations produce the same ID).
-- Open issue 2: The edge-case assertion ec_safe_2 (duplicate requests) may be too strong or underconstrained; its intended meaning might require additional structure.
-- Open issue 3: The model uses a linear chain of post-states (Pre1->Post1->Post2->Post3) but does not enforce that ordering; it is only suggestive in the reachability predicates.


